Challenges and Solutions
 Describe at least one challenge you faced and how you solved it.


One challenge I had was figuring out how to generate a Sudoku board without just hardcoding everything. At first I thought about randomly placing numbers, but that made it really hard to make sure the board was valid. Instead, I used a pattern where I filled in the first row and then shifted the numbers for each new row. This made it a lot easier and guaranteed the board didn’t break the rules.
